                <head>Riga, Russia</head>
                <p>John P. Hurley, Consul, Cl. 7, lately at Reval proceeded Riga and opened
                    Consulate Feb. 28, 1920: assigned Riga June 23, 1920</p>
                <p>Harold B. Quarton, Consul, Cl. 6, lately at Viborg, was detailed Riga March 1,
                    1922 for duty with the American Commissioner</p>
                <p><unclear>Rappats</unclear> Consul, Class 5 Aug. 28, 1920 assigned to Reval Oct.
                    14, 1922</p>
